    <h3 id="the-web-server" class="display-4 text-xs-center text-muted p-y-2"><a href="#the-web-server"><u>1. The Web Server</u></a></h3>

    <div class="jumbotron p-a-1">
      <p class="lead">To fully utilize the potential of Node and ES7, we've used Koa <span class="tag tag-primary">2.x</span> (by <a href="https://github.com/tj" target="_blank" data-toggle="tooltip" title="TJ is also the author of Express!">TJ Holowaychuk</a>), the spiritual successor to the <a href="http://expressjs.com/" target="_blank">Express framework</a>, and added everything to it you would need for a modern application; MVC architecture, <a href="https://github.com/koajs/csrf" target="_blank">CSRF</a> and <a href="https://github.com/venables/koa-helmet" target="_blank">XSS</a> protection, <a href="https://github.com/scttcper/koa-simple-ratelimit" target="_blank">rate limiting</a>, <a href="https://github.com/niftylettuce/koa-manifest-rev" target="_blank">manifest asset revisioning</a>, <a href="https://github.com/koajs/generic-session" target="_blank">sessions</a> (backed by <a href="https://github.com/koajs/koa-redis" target="_blank">Redis</a>), <a href="https://github.com/theverything/koa-connect-flash" target="_blank">flash messaging</a>, <a href="https://github.com/yosuke-furukawa/koa-livereload" target="_blank">LiveReload</a>, and more.</p>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-block">
              <p class="lead">We automatically enable stage-0 ES6/ES7 features.  You can simply <code>import</code> models in your controllers, and <code>import</code> controllers in your routes.</p>
              <pre class="js"><code>import Router from 'koa-router';

import controllers from '../../app/controllers';
import { renderPage, Policies } from '../../helpers';

const router = new Router();

router
  .get('/', renderPage('home'))
  .get('/about', renderPage('about'))
  .get('/status', controllers.web.status)
  // ...
  .get(
    '/signup',
    Policies.ensureLoggedOut,
    controllers.web.signupOrLogin
  );

export default router;</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-block">
              <p class="lead">To rid of <a href="http://callbackhell.com/" target="_blank">callback hell</a>, and write more readable, maintainable code &ndash; we use <a href="https://ponyfoo.com/articles/understanding-javascript-async-await" target="_blank">Async/Await</a>.</p>
              <p class="text-xs-center text-uppercase text-muted"><small>Before</small></p>
              <pre class="js"><code>function updateUser(req, res, next) {
  Users.findOne({ org: 'crocodilejs' }, function(err, user) {
    if (err) return next(err);
    if (!user) return next(new Error('User does not exist'));
    user.group = 'admin';
    user.save(function(err, user) {
      if (err) return next(err);
      res.json(user);
    });
  });
}</code></pre>
              <p class="text-xs-center text-uppercase text-muted"><small>After</small></p>
              <pre class="js"><code>static async updateUser(ctx) {
  let user = await User.findOne({ org: 'crocodilejs' });
  if (!user) return ctx.throw(Boom.badRequest('User does not exist'));
  user.group = 'admin';
  ctx.body = await user.save();
}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="alert alert-success text-xs-center"><small>Use the built-in templating language <a href="https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/" target="_blank">Nunjucks</a>, or plug in any front-end (such as <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react/" target="_blank">React</a>, <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react-native/" target="_blank">React Native</a>, or <a href="https://github.com/yoshuawuyts/choo" target="_blank">Choo</a>).</small></div>
      <p class="lead">We rode the {{ 'surfer' | emoji }} wave with Jade (now known as <a href="https://github.com/pugjs/pug" target="_blank">Pug</a>) for years... but then we found <a href="https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/" target="_blank">Nunjucks</a> to be extremely lightweight and faster in comparison.  Plus it is inspired by <a href="http://jinja.pocoo.org/docs/dev/" target="_blank">Jinja2</a>, which is amazing!  Of course, if you don't like Nunjucks, you can swap it out with <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react/" target="_blank">React</a>, <a href="https://github.com/pugjs/pug" target="_blank">Pug</a>, <a href="https://github.com/tj/ejs" target="_blank">EJS</a>, <a href="https://github.com/janl/mustache.js/" target="_blank">Mustache</a>, <a href="https://github.com/marko-js/marko" target="_blank">Marko</a> &ndash; whatever you want!  The default front-end consists of <a href="https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/" target="_blank">Nunjucks</a>, <a href="https://v4-alpha.getbootstrap.com/" target="_blank">Bootstrap 4</a>, AJAX form submission using <a href="https://github.com/crocodilejs/frisbee" target="_blank">Frisbee</a>, <a href="https://github.com/limonte/sweetalert2" target="_blank">SweetAlert2</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/tobiasahlin/SpinKit" target="_blank">SpinKit</a>, <a href="https://github.com/gocom/dense" target="_blank">dense</a> and <a href="https://github.com/eisbehr-/jquery.lazy" target="_blank">jquery-lazy</a> for automatic retina image support, <a href="https://github.com/yosuke-furukawa/koa-livereload" target="_blank">LiveReload</a>, and much more.</p>
