      <p class="lead">With inspiration from <a href="https://stripe.com" target="_blank">Stripe</a> (namely <a href="http://www.amberfeng.com/" target="_blank">Amber Feng</a>), and years of experience building developer-friendly API's &ndash; we've crafted a RESTful API that is simple to use, secure, and documented.  <strong>You can even try it out right now from your terminal (see below)</strong>.  It supports versioning, BasicAuth token access (automatically generated for users and available on the <a href="/my-account">My Account</a> page), rate limiting, and beautiful API responses (even for errors thanks to <a href="https://github.com/hapijs/boom" target="_blank">Boom</a>). It's absolutely perfect for building the back-end of your <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react-native/" target="_blank">React Native</a>, <a href="https://github.com/electron/electron" target="_blank">Electron</a>, iOS, or Android app.  You have full control of everything; you don't need to rely on a third-party API platform provider.  You can finally stop reading convoluted documentation and start writing your API endpoints!</p>

